      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FEDERAL ESCAPE (4) hit the ground running with a slick early sectional but had to settle for a minor placing when a 1.75 lengths second over 300m at this track, clocking 17.16. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Deserves serious consideration. TODOROKI (1) missed the frame last time when fourth (17.66) at this track but prior to that had three placings in a row. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Better than last start and can bounce back. SWAY BAR (2) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Grafton over 350m behind She Lies Easy (20.60) in a Grade 5. Has ability and can atone. RIPPLE LINGER (3) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
